#: src/rust-2018/documentation/std-os-has-documentation-for-all-platforms.md:1
msgid "`std::os` has documentation for all platforms"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/std-os-has-documentation-for-all-platforms.md:3
msgid ""
"![Minimum Rust version: 1.21](https://img.shields.io/badge/"
"Minimum%20Rust%20Version-1.21-brightgreen.svg)"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/std-os-has-documentation-for-all-platforms.md:5
msgid ""
"The `std::os` module contains operating system specific functionality. "
"You’ll now see more than just linux, the platform we build the documentation "
"on."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/std-os-has-documentation-for-all-platforms.md:8
msgid ""
"We’ve long regretted that the hosted version of the documentation has been "
"Linux-specific; this is a first step towards rectifying that. This is "
"specific to the standard library and not for general use; we hope to improve "
"this further in the future."
msgstr ""
